The paper proposes a model that combines visual and textual content to address the cold start problem in sequential prediction. This involves learning sequential latent vectors that capture user interest and content-based representations to address the cold start. The model is based on a recurrent neural network (RNN) architecture. Given these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
